    "html": "\r\n<h1>\r\nHop In\r\n</h1>\r\n<b>Meaning/Usage</b>: Used to tell someone to get in the car<br><br> <b>Explanation</b>: &quot;Hop&quot; is like a small jump. &#xA0;So this phrase is pretty straightforward. <br><br>&quot;<a href=\"http://www.talkenglish.com/AudioTE1/P142/sentence/P142S1.mp3\"><b>Hop in</b>. &#xA0;You can ride with me to the grocery store.</a>&quot;<br>&quot;<a href=\"http://www.talkenglish.com/AudioTE1/P142/sentence/P142S2.mp3\"><b>Hop in</b>. &#xA0;We need to leave right away.</a>&quot;<br>&quot;<a href=\"http://www.talkenglish.com/AudioTE1/P142/sentence/P142S3.mp3\">If you need a ride home, <b>hop on in</b>.</a>&quot;<br><br><b>A.</b> &#xA0;&quot;<a href=\"http://www.talkenglish.com/AudioTE1/P142/sentence/P142S4.mp3\">I can&apos;t believe my car broke down again.</a>&quot;<br><b>B.</b> &#xA0;&quot;<a href=\"http://www.talkenglish.com/AudioTE1/P142/sentence/P142S5.mp3\"><b>Hop in</b>, and I&apos;ll give you a ride home.</a>&quot;<br><b>A.</b> &#xA0;&quot;<a href=\"http://www.talkenglish.com/AudioTE1/P142/sentence/P142S6.mp3\">Thanks man.</a>&quot;<br><b>B.</b> &#xA0;&quot;<a href=\"http://www.talkenglish.com/AudioTE1/P142/sentence/P142S7.mp3\">You&apos;re welcome.</a>&quot;<br><br>Other Common Sentences<br><br>&quot;<a href=\"http://www.talkenglish.com/AudioTE1/P142/sentence/P142S8.mp3\">Get in the car.</a>&quot;<br>&quot;<a href=\"http://www.talkenglish.com/AudioTE1/P142/sentence/P142S9.mp3\">Jump in the car</a>&quot;<br><br>\r\n"
